@startuml client_server_component_refactored
top to bottom direction
title iDaVIE — Target Component Diagram\nClient–Server + Micro-Kernel + Layered + Versioned C ABI Plug-ins\n(per Assignment Spec §4 — Sub-team 1, Apaties I)

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam nodesep 15
skinparam ranksep 25
skinparam component {
    BackgroundColor White
    BorderColor #444444
    ArrowColor #444444
    FontSize 11
}
skinparam interface {
    BackgroundColor #E8F4E8
    BorderColor #2E7D32
}
skinparam package {
    BackgroundColor #FAFAFA
    BorderColor #999999
    FontSize 12
    FontStyle bold
}
skinparam note {
    BackgroundColor #FFFDE7
    BorderColor #F9A825
}
skinparam arrow {
    Color #444444
}

' =================================================================
' CLIENT  — Unity 6 process: rendering, input, presentation only.
'           Domain logic and plug-in execution live on the SERVER.
' =================================================================
package "iDaVIE Client  (Unity 6 process)" #E8F0FF {

    package "Desktop GUI Subsystem  [Sub-team 6 — MVVM]" #D8F0FF {
        [CanvassDesktop View\n«Unity 6 UI Toolkit»]      as DesktopView
        [Desktop ViewModel\n«pure C# — no Unity refs»]   as DesktopVM
        [Menu ViewModels\nHistogram / Spectral / Moment /\nShape / Paint / Video] as MenuVMs
    }

    package "VR Interaction Subsystem  [Sub-team 4]" #D8F0FF {
        [LocomotionState\n«pure C# state pattern»]       as LocState
        [InteractionState\n«pure C# state pattern»]      as IntState
        [VoiceCommandDispatcher\n«Command pattern»]      as VoiceDisp
        interface "IInputProvider"     as IIP
        interface "IPointer"           as IPtr
        interface "IGripInput"         as IGrip
        interface "IVoiceInput"        as IVI
        interface "IHaptics"           as IH
        interface "IVoiceRecogniser"   as IVR
    }

    package "VR Rendering Subsystem  [Sub-team 3]" #D8F0FF {
        [VolumeMaterialBinder\n«pure C#»]               as VMB
        [VolumeTextureManager]                          as VTM
        [VolumeCameraDriver]                            as VCD
        [FoveatedSamplingPolicy\n«pure C# Strategy»]    as FSP
        [FeatureVisualiser\n«Unity-side adapter»]       as FVis
        [CatalogVisualiser]                             as CVis
        interface "IRenderPipeline"  as IRP
        interface "IMaskMode\n(Apply / Inverse / Isolate)" as IMM
    }

    ' ─── Anti-Corruption Layer  (§4.1, ADR-007) ───────────────────
    package "Anti-Corruption Layer  [Sub-team 1]" #C8E0FF {
        [SteamVRInputAdapter\n«only file that imports SteamVR»]   as ACL_SVR
        [UnityInputSystemAdapter\n«new Unity 6 Input System»]     as ACL_UIS
        [UnityKeywordRecogniserAdapter\n«Windows Speech»]         as ACL_VR
        [URP/HDRP RenderPipelineAdapter]                          as ACL_RP
        [UIToolkitBridge\n«Unity 6 UI Toolkit binding»]           as ACL_UI
    }

    ' Internal client wiring (all dependencies cross interfaces)
    DesktopView   --> DesktopVM            : data binding
    DesktopView   --> MenuVMs              : panel binding
    DesktopVM     --> ACL_UI               : presentation events
    LocState      ..> IIP                  : reads
    IntState      ..> IIP                  : reads
    LocState      ..> IPtr
    IntState      ..> IGrip
    IntState      ..> IH
    VoiceDisp     ..> IVR
    LocState      --> VCD                  : camera state
    IntState      --> VMB                  : mask / render cmd
    VMB           ..> IRP
    VMB           ..> IMM
    VTM           ..> IRP
    DesktopVM     --> VMB                  : colour map / threshold

    ' Anti-corruption layer realises every Unity-touching interface
    ACL_SVR ..|> IIP
    ACL_SVR ..|> IPtr
    ACL_SVR ..|> IGrip
    ACL_SVR ..|> IH
    ACL_UIS ..|> IIP
    ACL_VR  ..|> IVR
    ACL_RP  ..|> IRP
}

' =================================================================
' CLIENT ↔ SERVER  contract  (the only seam across the wire)
' =================================================================
package "Service Gateway  [Sub-teams 1 + 6]" #DDEEFF {
    [ServiceGateway (client proxy)\n«generated stub»]  as ClientGW
    interface "Client Service Contract\n──────────────────────\nIVolumeLoader\nICoordinateSystem\nIStatisticsService\nITextureFactory\nIMaskEditor\nIDataExporter\nIFeatureCatalogClient\nIWorkspaceStoreClient" as IClientSvc
    ClientGW ..|> IClientSvc
}

DesktopVM --> ClientGW : load / export / stats
MenuVMs   --> ClientGW : analysis triggers
VMB       --> ClientGW : request subcube / textures
FVis      --> ClientGW : feature reads / edits
VoiceDisp --> ClientGW : voice commands

cloud "Transport\n──────────────────\n«ADR-001»\nJSON-RPC over named pipes (local)\ngRPC over TCP/TLS (remote)" as Wire
ClientGW -down-> Wire : marshals

' =================================================================
' SERVER  — Micro-Kernel
'   Strict downward layering:
'     Domain  →  Application  →  Infrastructure  →  Plug-in Host
'   (§4.1, §6.1, ADR-006)
' =================================================================
package "iDaVIE Server  (Micro-Kernel, Sub-team 1)" #FFF0E8 {

    ' ───── Domain layer (no Unity, no SteamVR, no URP/HDRP) ─────
    package "Domain Layer\n[no UnityEngine / SteamVR refs — §4.2.3]" #FFD8C0 {
        [VolumeDataSet\n«aggregate root»]      as VDS
        [VolumeDataCore\n«value object»]       as VDC
        [Subcube\n«value object»]              as SubVO
        [Mask\n«entity»]                       as MaskE
        [WCSCoordinateSystem\n«value object»]  as WCSVO
        [Feature\n«aggregate root» — Sub-team 5] as FeatE
        [FeatureCatalog\n«domain service» — Sub-team 5] as FCat
        [Workspace\n«aggregate root» — Sub-team 7] as WS

        VDS *-- VDC
        VDS *-- MaskE
        VDS o-- WCSVO
        FCat o-- FeatE
        WS  o-- VDS
        WS  o-- FCat
    }

    ' ───── Application layer (use cases / orchestration) ─────
    package "Application Layer  [use cases]" #FFE8D8 {
        [LoadFitsCubeUseCase]      as UC_Load
        [RequestSubcubeUseCase]    as UC_Sub
        [ExportMaskUseCase]        as UC_Exp
        [ComputeStatisticsUseCase] as UC_Stats
        [MomentMapUseCase]         as UC_Moment
        [SpectralProfileUseCase]   as UC_Spec
        [PaintMaskUseCase]         as UC_Paint
        [FeatureSetService\n«Sub-team 5»] as UC_Feat
        [WorkspaceService\n«Sub-team 7»]  as UC_WS
    }

    ' ───── Infrastructure layer (adapters, repositories, gateway) ─────
    package "Infrastructure Layer" #FFE0D0 {
        [ServiceGatewayEndpoint\n«JSON-RPC / gRPC server»] as ServerGW
        [WorkspaceRepository]                             as WSRepo
        [FeatureCatalogRepository]                        as FCRepo
        [VolumeTextureFactoryImpl]                        as VTFImpl
        [StructuredLoggingSink]                           as Logger
        [ConfigStore]                                     as CfgStore
    }
    ServerGW ..|> IClientSvc

    ' ───── Plug-in Host (kernel boundary) ─────
    package "Plug-in Host  (kernel boundary)" #FFD8B8 {
        [PluginRegistry\n«Service Locator»\nGRASP: Indirection, Protected Variations\n«ADR-008»] as Registry
        [PluginLoader\n«hot-reload, fault-isolation»]    as Loader
        interface "IPluginABI v1.x\n«C ABI — semver, ABI-stable»\n«ADR-002, ADR-003, ADR-004, ADR-005»" as IABI
        Registry ..> IABI : resolves
        Loader   --> Registry : registers
    }

    ' Strict downward dependencies (Application → Domain;
    ' Infrastructure → Application/Domain; Plug-in Host below all)
    ServerGW --> UC_Load
    ServerGW --> UC_Sub
    ServerGW --> UC_Exp
    ServerGW --> UC_Stats
    ServerGW --> UC_Moment
    ServerGW --> UC_Spec
    ServerGW --> UC_Paint
    ServerGW --> UC_Feat
    ServerGW --> UC_WS

    UC_Load   --> VDS
    UC_Sub    --> VDS
    UC_Exp    --> VDS
    UC_Stats  --> VDS
    UC_Moment --> VDS
    UC_Spec   --> VDS
    UC_Paint  --> MaskE
    UC_Feat   --> FCat
    UC_WS     --> WS

    UC_Load   --> WSRepo
    UC_WS     --> WSRepo
    UC_Feat   --> FCRepo
    UC_Sub    --> VTFImpl

    WSRepo  ..> WS    : persists
    FCRepo  ..> FCat  : persists
    VTFImpl ..> VDS   : reads voxels

    ' Use cases resolve plug-ins through the registry (constructor-injected
    ' inside the kernel; Service Locator only at the boundary).
    UC_Load   ..> Registry : "fits-reader"
    UC_Load   ..> Registry : "wcs-transform"
    UC_Sub    ..> Registry : "downsampler"
    UC_Stats  ..> Registry : "statistics"
    UC_Exp    ..> Registry : "fits-writer"
    UC_Feat   ..> Registry : "source-finder"
}

' =================================================================
' PLUG-INS  — behind the versioned C ABI  (Sub-team 2)
'   Split into data-format vs data-operation per §6.2,
'   grouped together so they always render as one cluster.
' =================================================================
package "Plug-in Cluster  (loaded by the kernel through IPluginABI)" #FFE8D0 {

    package "Data-Format Plug-ins  [Sub-team 2]" #FFE0CC {
        [fits-reader.so / .dll]   as PFR
        [fits-writer.so / .dll]   as PFW
        [votable.so / .dll]       as PVO
        [tiff.so / .dll]          as PTIFF
    }

    package "Data-Operation Plug-ins  [Sub-team 2]" #FFE0CC {
        [wcs-transform.so / .dll] as PWCS
        [statistics.so / .dll]    as PStats
        [downsampler.so / .dll]   as PDS
        [source-finder.so / .dll] as PSF
    }

    package "Third-Party C++ Libraries" #FFD0BB {
        [CFITSIO]            as CFITSIO
        [Starlink AST]       as SAST
        [cminpack / OpenMP]  as CMINPACK
    }
}

' Plug-ins realise the versioned C ABI
PFR    ..|> IABI
PFW    ..|> IABI
PVO    ..|> IABI
PTIFF  ..|> IABI
PWCS   ..|> IABI
PStats ..|> IABI
PDS    ..|> IABI
PSF    ..|> IABI

' Plug-ins wrap third-party C++ libs
PFR    --> CFITSIO
PFW    --> CFITSIO
PVO    --> CFITSIO
PWCS   --> SAST
PStats --> CMINPACK
PDS    --> CMINPACK
PSF    --> CMINPACK

' Hidden layout hints — minimal: just anchor the major regions.
'   Client (top)  →  Transport  →  Server  →  Plug-in Cluster (bottom)
ClientGW -[hidden]down- Wire
Wire     -[hidden]down- ServerGW
Registry -[hidden]down- PFR
PFR      -[hidden]down- CFITSIO

' =================================================================
' Architectural-rationale notes (anchor to spec sections + ADRs)
' =================================================================
note as N1
  **Architectural style — Assignment spec §4**
  • Client–server split at the system level (this diagram).
  • Micro-kernel server with a versioned C ABI plug-in contract.
  • Strict layered architecture inside the kernel:
      Domain → Application → Infrastructure → Plug-in Host.
  • Anti-Corruption Layer wraps every Unity 6 / SteamVR /
    URP / HDRP / UI Toolkit type so domain logic stays
    Unity-free and testable outside Unity.
end note

note as N2
  **Mandatory constraints (§4.2) — how this diagram honours them**
  1. **SOLID/GRASP**: every cross-component edge is an interface;
     ISP-segregated VR inputs (IPointer/IGrip/IVoice/IHaptics);
     Service Locator confined to the kernel boundary.
  2. **No cycles**: every arrow either points downward through the
     layer stack or across an interface boundary. Domain has
     fan-in only.
  3. **Domain Unity-free**: only the Anti-Corruption Layer and the
     three Unity-side adapters (Visualisers, View, MonoBehaviour
     bridges) import UnityEngine / SteamVR / URP / HDRP.
  4. **Interface + test double at every boundary**: green lozenges
     mark the contracts; each one has a fake/mock in the test suite.
  5. **Versioned plug-in C ABI**: IPluginABI v1.x is semver-versioned
     and ABI-stable within a major version (ADR-002 / 003 / 004 / 005).
end note

note as N3
  **Transport contract — ADR-001**
  • Local mode: JSON-RPC over a named pipe.
    Same process today, separable tomorrow.
  • Remote mode: gRPC over TCP/TLS, schema generated
    from the shared .proto contract.
  • The Service Gateway is the **only** seam across the wire;
    no other component crosses client/server.
end note

note as N4
  **Sub-team ownership — integration spine**
  • **Sub-team 1 (Apaties I — us)**: kernel boundary, plug-in ABI,
    Anti-Corruption Layer, layer-violation CI rules, Service Gateway.
  • **Sub-team 2**: data-format + data-operation plug-ins.
  • **Sub-team 3**: rendering subsystem + IRenderPipeline ACL.
  • **Sub-team 4**: interaction subsystem + IInputProvider et al.
  • **Sub-team 5**: Feature aggregate, FeatureCatalog,
    FeatureSetService, FeatureVisualiser.
  • **Sub-team 6**: Desktop GUI MVVM + client Service Gateway.
  • **Sub-team 7**: Workspace aggregate + persistence repositories.
end note

@enduml
